- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses recurrent neural networks to parameterize the models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing a model that can generate outputs that explain their inputs. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks to model the source and channel. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely as the paper does not deal with image or video data, but it is still possible as the paper uses beam search decoding, which is a common technique in computer vision.
